                    <span>   To treat Tabloid TV seriously is like trying to treat Daytime TV as a serious art form.  There is no special reason why Tabloid TV has become big business, the Television networks as a whole always wanted rateings.  That is what drove the business.  To do shows that were all the rage at the moment.  If people watched them, you made more of the same thing.  If they watched westerns, You Made Westerns, if they wanted Game Shows, you would make a ton of Game shows, and so on. Tabloid news only came about because people liked to read tabloid papers, and with Cable TV taking over like it did, Media excutives decided to do more yellow journalism shows and put them on cable as fast as they could.  Network TV was never all that great to start with.  It was called a wasteland when it started and it still is.   It's sad, ad it is repulsive,  to ignore it is the only sane thing to do.  Support PBS instead. </span>
                  
              
